The NFL Extra Points Credit Card is designed for football fans who want to earn rewards on NFL tickets and NFL-branded merchandise, along with access to special discounts and ticket financing. However, you’ll earn a relatively low rewards rate on all other purchases, and the card carries costly balance transfer fees.
 Earn 10,000 bonus points after $500 in purchases in the first 90 days, enough to redeem $100 cash back. The NFL Extra Points Credit Card is not one of our top-rated rewards credit cards. You can review our list of the best rewards credit cards for what we think are better options. 10,000-point one-time offer Extra rewards on NFL and team purchases Special ticket financing Low rewards on non-NFL purchases Redemption points minimum Balance transfer fees 
The NFL Extra Points Credit Card is best for diehard football fans who want to earn rewards on NFL and team purchases. If you regularly attend games or buy team merchandise, you can earn 2 points per $1 on those purchases. In addition, you’ll get 20% off every $100 you spend at NFLShop.com. Cardholders can also qualify for special ticket financing, allowing them to spread out the cost of tickets over several months. 
 
With the NFL Extra Points Credit Card, you can earn a 10,000-point bonus if you spend $500 on purchases within the first 90 days of opening an account, a $100 value. 
 
You’ll earn the following rewards on your purchases: 
 
You can redeem your points for NFL and team gift cards, NFL and team experiences, NFL tickets, statement credits, and bank deposits. You must have accumulated at least 2,500 points before you can redeem your rewards. To redeem rewards, visit MyNFLCard.com. 
